ENTRY            A0010   20260125   20260317   20260317       A129
SUBENT        A0010001   20260125   20260317   20260317       A129
BIB                 14         33
TITLE      Synthesis of 260Rf in the irradiation of 149Bk
           by 15N ions
AUTHOR     (V.A.Druin, B.Bochev, Ju.V.Lobanov, E.A.Minin,
           Ju.V.Polubojarinov, A.G.Rykov, R.N.Sagajdak,
           S.P.Tret'jakova, Ju.P.Kharitonov)
REFERENCE  (J,SJA,43,785,1977) English translation
           (J,AE,43,155,1977)
           (R,JINR-E7-10499,1977)
INSTITUTE  (4ZZZDUB)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,4ZZZDUB)
SAMPLE     Pure Bk-249, about 180 ug/cm2.
METHOD     (REC,BCINT,SITA,EXTB)
DETECTOR   (GLASD)
ANALYSIS   Least-squares method using standard code.
           The results of two series of experiments.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty
REL-REF    (N,,A.S.Il'inov,R,JINR-P7-7108,1973) Experimental
           results of the present work is compared with
           theoretical calculation for Bk-249(N-15,4n)104-Rf-260
           reaction, which in this preprint is given.
           (N,,A.Ghiorso,C,76CORSICA,,,197605) Results of the
           present work is compared with Ghiorso's results.
ADD-RES    (RANGE,COMP) Time distribution of fission fragments
           tracks by bombarding 249Bk with 15N ions is discussed.
           The negative result of Berkeley experiments on the
           detection of spontaneous fission activity due to
           Rf-260 is analysed and the sources of errors are
           given.
STATUS     (CURVE,,V.A.Druin+,J,SJA,43,785,1977) By CaJAD.
           (APRVD) By V.A.Druin.
HISTORY    (19771129C)
           (20080608A) BIB section updated
           (20260125A) SD: Corrections in Subent 001.
ENDBIB              33
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           36
